            "body": ">I think we'd just call the argument `if_` - that sort of name is fairly\n>common elsewhere in the Python world.\n\nSorry for the bike shedding, but requiring underscore names for keyword arguments seems unnecessarily annoying. I'm sure there's a nicer name. Maybe \"only_if\"? I'm not sure if that's better, but at least it doesn't look like we just failed to find a better name.\n",
