        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I partially agree, but the clear reference to the openmp specification is obvious when using this name. I will not object to any choice.  \r\nBut I would prefer a clear nomenclature resembling the openmp specification. \r\n\r\nI would also think that people trying out Cython would quite quickly realize that `if` is a reserved word, hence the _, it is not uncommon practice, take https://docs.python.org/3/library/operator.html as an example.",
            "created_at": "2023-04-19T15:00:25Z",
