        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> I would also think that people trying out Cython would quite quickly realize that `if` is a reserved word, hence the _, it is not uncommon practice\r\n\r\nYes - that was largely my logic in suggesting it. Similar things seem to be the de-facto way of writing names that conflict with keywords (PyQt `exec_` was in my mind as an example too).\r\n\r\nWith that said, I don't feel too strongly and would be happy with other sensible options. If/when you have something you're close to happy with, don't delay submitting it because you're unsure of a name.",
